WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.068 --> 00:00:03.246
Viewers like you make
this program possible.

2
00:00:03.270 --> 00:00:05.339
Support your local PBS station.

3
00:00:45.146 --> 00:00:46.256
Cheers.

4
00:00:46.280 --> 00:00:47.447
My pleasure. Vicar.

5
00:00:53.654 --> 00:00:55.856
I can't get my head around it.

6
00:00:57.124 --> 00:00:58.769
Tilly Mayflower?

7
00:00:58.793 --> 00:01:03.006
The model of the moment.
will be wearing a CeCe's dress.

8
00:01:03.030 --> 00:01:05.942
But she usually wears Courreges.

9
00:01:05.966 --> 00:01:08.044
We can't compete with this.

10
00:01:08.068 --> 00:01:10.313
Wouldn't take much more
than a small gust of wind

11
00:01:10.337 --> 00:01:11.982
to sweep her clean away.

12
00:01:12.006 --> 00:01:14.551
Soon you'll be able to get
CeCe's onto the King's Road.

13
00:01:14.575 --> 00:01:16.119
And after that. who knows?

14
00:01:16.143 --> 00:01:17.421
Paris. New York.

15
00:01:17.445 --> 00:01:20.290
Steady on. How about
we trot back to reality.

16
00:01:20.314 --> 00:01:22.192
At the end of the day
a good business

17
00:01:22.216 --> 00:01:24.718
is about turnover
and making profit.

18
00:01:25.553 --> 00:01:27.330
I trust you sent the bill.

19
00:01:27.354 --> 00:01:29.499
We can't be delivering garments
with no payment.

20
00:01:29.523 --> 00:01:30.667
We're not a charity.

21
00:01:30.691 --> 00:01:33.270
Tilly Mayflower
in a CeCe's dress

22
00:01:33.294 --> 00:01:34.961
is an opportunity
not to be missed.

23
00:01:36.931 --> 00:01:38.198
She's changed her mind.

24
00:01:41.535 --> 00:01:43.437
-Cathy.
-Oh.

25
00:01:46.474 --> 00:01:48.952
{\an8}Hello. CeCe's Boutique...

26
00:01:48.976 --> 00:01:50.420
{\an8}Cathy speaking... Keating...

27
00:01:50.444 --> 00:01:52.722
Uh... Cathy Keating speaking.

28
00:01:52.746 --> 00:01:53.914
How may I help?

29
00:01:55.216 --> 00:01:57.017
{\an8}Oh. hello.

30
00:01:58.152 --> 00:02:00.864
{\an8}Really? Okay.

31
00:02:00.888 --> 00:02:02.690
{\an8}No. no. not a problem.

32
00:02:04.258 --> 00:02:05.559
{\an8}Yes. I do.

33
00:02:06.360 --> 00:02:07.595
{\an8}Oh... bye then.

34
00:02:09.396 --> 00:02:11.274
{\an8}Tilly Mayflower won't have time
to come to the shop

35
00:02:11.298 --> 00:02:13.043
{\an8}-for a fitting.
-Typical.

36
00:02:13.067 --> 00:02:15.412
{\an8}Instead her manager has asked us

37
00:02:15.436 --> 00:02:19.149
{\an8}to take the dress to her
this evening at Sady's.

38
00:02:19.173 --> 00:02:20.217
{\an8}Oh...

39
00:02:20.241 --> 00:02:21.518
{\an8}Where on earth is that?

40
00:02:21.542 --> 00:02:23.987
{\an8}Well. it's the new private
members club in Cambridge.

41
00:02:24.011 --> 00:02:25.021
{\an8}Very elite.

42
00:02:25.045 --> 00:02:26.923
{\an8}And what if the dress
doesn't fit? What then?

43
00:02:26.947 --> 00:02:28.859
{\an8}These people.
they just expect you

44
00:02:28.883 --> 00:02:31.895
{\an8}to do their bidding
with their fancy places

45
00:02:31.919 --> 00:02:33.063
{\an8}and their fancy ideas.

46
00:02:33.087 --> 00:02:35.832
{\an8}-I can go.
-No need.

47
00:02:35.856 --> 00:02:36.900
{\an8}I'll go.

48
00:02:36.924 --> 00:02:37.868
{\an8}I thought we were having

49
00:02:37.892 --> 00:02:40.370
{\an8}-supper with the Browns?
-They'll understand.

50
00:02:40.394 --> 00:02:42.396
{\an8}It's a bit
late in the day. Sylvia.

51
00:02:43.297 --> 00:02:44.841
{\an8}I'll telephone them now.

52
00:02:44.865 --> 00:02:46.176
{\an8}Uh. uh. uh...

53
00:02:46.200 --> 00:02:48.345
{\an8}You go and enjoy yourself.
Mrs C.

54
00:02:48.369 --> 00:02:50.580
{\an8}Mrs Chapman.

55
00:02:50.604 --> 00:02:54.618
{\an8}Apologies. You go
and enjoy yourself. Mrs Chapman.

56
00:02:54.642 --> 00:02:57.687
{\an8}-Cathy and I can handle this.
-Of course they can.

57
00:02:57.711 --> 00:02:59.122
What did I tell you?

58
00:02:59.146 --> 00:03:02.048
You better get used
to that champagne lifestyle.

59
00:03:03.751 --> 00:03:05.019
Oh. crikey.

60
00:03:05.953 --> 00:03:07.564
I need to get a move on.

61
00:03:07.588 --> 00:03:09.733
Uh... I'm going
to need to change.

62
00:03:09.757 --> 00:03:11.434
I haven't got time to go home.

63
00:03:11.458 --> 00:03:13.870
Best let Geordie know
he'll be making his own supper.

64
00:03:13.894 --> 00:03:16.806
Don't be daft.
He's perfectly capable.

65
00:03:16.830 --> 00:03:20.534
Still. a man has the right
to know where his wife is...

66
00:03:22.503 --> 00:03:23.871
and with whom.

67
00:03:36.850 --> 00:03:38.562
Sorry to bother you. Boss.

68
00:03:38.586 --> 00:03:41.164
We've just had a call
from Mrs Lewis.

69
00:03:41.188 --> 00:03:42.890
She thinks Gerald's been taken.

70
00:03:43.324 --> 00:03:44.534
Who's Gerald?

71
00:03:44.558 --> 00:03:45.593
Her cat.

72
00:03:47.194 --> 00:03:48.338
You're joking.

73
00:03:48.362 --> 00:03:51.341
I know. but she sounded
quite distressed

74
00:03:51.365 --> 00:03:54.911
and she has just
lost her husband.

75
00:03:54.935 --> 00:03:57.247
Can a man not eat
the cheese and pickle sandwich

76
00:03:57.271 --> 00:03:58.606
in peace?

77
00:04:12.186 --> 00:04:14.655
So. Vicar. should we be worried?

78
00:04:15.456 --> 00:04:17.024
You do have God on your side.

79
00:04:18.092 --> 00:04:19.603
I'm an atheist.

80
00:04:19.627 --> 00:04:21.805
God's no poker player.

81
00:04:21.829 --> 00:04:24.708
Don't worry about him. Vicar.
He can't handle his booze.

82
00:04:24.732 --> 00:04:25.899
It's Alphy.

83
00:04:28.369 --> 00:04:29.770
Call me Alphy.

84
00:04:40.247 --> 00:04:42.016
Oh.

85
00:04:46.520 --> 00:04:48.064
Is it always
this quiet. Malcolm?

86
00:04:48.088 --> 00:04:51.001
No. no. sir. No. we've actually
been quite busy since we opened.

87
00:04:51.025 --> 00:04:52.936
However. Miss Mayflower's agent

88
00:04:52.960 --> 00:04:54.904
requested that we close
the club this evening.

89
00:04:54.928 --> 00:04:56.239
for her privacy.

90
00:04:56.263 --> 00:04:58.074
She has rather the following
of photographers.

91
00:04:58.098 --> 00:05:01.501
And we strive for discretion
for our guests here at Sady's.

92
00:05:07.441 --> 00:05:11.879
I believe you are the lady
responsible for this.

93
00:05:17.084 --> 00:05:18.085
Yes.

94
00:05:19.153 --> 00:05:21.498
It's fabulous. darling.

95
00:05:21.522 --> 00:05:23.366
Clarke Barron. Tilly's manager.

96
00:05:23.390 --> 00:05:25.735
Muah. Muah.

97
00:05:25.759 --> 00:05:26.870
Switch.

98
00:05:26.894 --> 00:05:28.204
I love it.

99
00:05:28.228 --> 00:05:30.674
Oh. I've been so worried.

100
00:05:30.698 --> 00:05:33.243
I've never done
a blind fitting before.

101
00:05:33.267 --> 00:05:34.511
And for someone like you.

102
00:05:34.535 --> 00:05:38.048
It's wonderful. really. Mrs...

103
00:05:38.072 --> 00:05:41.451
Please call me Cathy.

104
00:05:41.475 --> 00:05:43.987
Oh. Malcolm. will you bring us
a couple of bottles

105
00:05:44.011 --> 00:05:45.255
of your finest champagne?

106
00:05:45.279 --> 00:05:46.756
-Ice cold.
-Of course. sir.

107
00:05:46.780 --> 00:05:49.559
This is Kara.
Our wonderful hostess.

108
00:05:49.583 --> 00:05:50.760
She'll be looking
after you this evening.

109
00:05:50.784 --> 00:05:53.196
Anything you need.
Miss Mayflower. Mrs Keating.

110
00:05:53.220 --> 00:05:54.387
please don't hesitate to ask.

111
00:05:57.324 --> 00:05:58.568
Champagne.

112
00:05:58.592 --> 00:06:00.236
That's extremely
generous of you.

113
00:06:00.260 --> 00:06:01.604
The dress was a steal.

114
00:06:01.628 --> 00:06:04.474
We should have charged
you more then.

115
00:06:04.498 --> 00:06:05.575
It's good for Tilly's image

116
00:06:05.599 --> 00:06:08.144
to be seen
to support local enterprises.

117
00:06:08.168 --> 00:06:09.312
You wouldn't believe

118
00:06:09.336 --> 00:06:11.581
that models need to be
more than just a...

119
00:06:11.605 --> 00:06:14.084
face and a body these days.

120
00:06:14.108 --> 00:06:16.843
It's so unbelievably tedious.

121
00:06:18.545 --> 00:06:19.780
When can we leave?

122
00:06:20.447 --> 00:06:21.949
I'm tired. Clarkey.

123
00:06:22.850 --> 00:06:24.250
I'll get you an espresso.

124
00:06:26.687 --> 00:06:28.054
-Ah.
-Oh.

125
00:06:30.157 --> 00:06:32.836
-Mmm.
-Mmm...

126
00:06:32.860 --> 00:06:37.163
I think we can safely say
that this is a big success.

127
00:06:39.867 --> 00:06:40.910
What's going on?

128
00:06:40.934 --> 00:06:42.645
She doesn't seem very happy.

129
00:06:42.669 --> 00:06:43.713
Don't be fooled by that

130
00:06:43.737 --> 00:06:46.038
"too cool for school"
model look.

131
00:06:49.943 --> 00:06:51.044
Cheers.

132
00:06:58.085 --> 00:06:59.262
Oh. my word.

133
00:06:59.286 --> 00:07:02.022
I told you.
you'd better get used to it.

134
00:07:03.157 --> 00:07:04.625
This is just the beginning.

135
00:07:18.639 --> 00:07:19.807
Raise.

136
00:07:25.245 --> 00:07:27.381
I'm out.

137
00:07:28.182 --> 00:07:29.282
I'm out. too.

138
00:07:45.632 --> 00:07:46.700
Still in.

139
00:07:48.335 --> 00:07:49.570
Good man.

140
00:07:52.739 --> 00:07:55.652
Cilla's just got
the most adorable voice.

141
00:07:55.676 --> 00:07:58.721
And she's my age!
Oh. she's gonna be a star.

142
00:07:58.745 --> 00:07:59.812
I'm sure of it.

143
00:08:01.782 --> 00:08:04.360
-She does have potential.
-Mmm.

144
00:08:04.384 --> 00:08:07.019
Oh. Bubbles
go straight to my head.

145
00:08:08.555 --> 00:08:10.023
I know. darling.

146
00:08:13.126 --> 00:08:14.170
What time is it?

147
00:08:14.194 --> 00:08:17.273
Oh. it's... coming up to 9:30.

148
00:08:17.297 --> 00:08:20.334
Oh. I should be getting home.

149
00:08:23.136 --> 00:08:24.137
Is everything all right?

150
00:08:25.205 --> 00:08:26.606
I'm going to find my coat.

151
00:08:37.651 --> 00:08:38.684
Malcolm?

152
00:08:42.189 --> 00:08:43.657
Oh. my God.

153
00:08:48.662 --> 00:08:51.230
Looks like it's just
the two of us again. Vicar.

154
00:08:54.801 --> 00:08:57.703
Still relying on
divine intervention.

155
00:09:05.646 --> 00:09:06.880
What's it gonna be. Alphy?

156
00:09:07.447 --> 00:09:09.081
You in or out?

157
00:09:20.427 --> 00:09:22.372
Should've stuck with it Alphy.

158
00:09:22.396 --> 00:09:24.698
I had absolutely nothing.

159
00:09:29.303 --> 00:09:31.270
Oh. that was
one hell of a bluff.

160
00:09:36.243 --> 00:09:38.612
Better luck next time. Alphy.

161
00:09:50.157 --> 00:09:51.658
What the hell
are you doing here?

162
00:09:52.192 --> 00:09:53.670
Oh. the dress.

163
00:09:53.694 --> 00:09:56.539
Tilly wanted us to come here

164
00:09:56.563 --> 00:09:57.907
instead of the shop.

165
00:09:57.931 --> 00:09:59.666
Mrs C's here as well?

166
00:10:00.634 --> 00:10:01.868
She couldn't make it.

167
00:10:12.980 --> 00:10:13.981
Who found him?

168
00:10:14.948 --> 00:10:15.949
I did.

169
00:10:34.501 --> 00:10:36.436
It stopped at 8:45.

170
00:10:38.672 --> 00:10:41.074
And nothing like a dead body
to sober you up. huh?

171
00:10:59.259 --> 00:11:00.436
Well. whoever strangled him

172
00:11:00.460 --> 00:11:02.495
didn't do it for the money.

173
00:11:22.516 --> 00:11:24.060
This is Kara Quenn.

174
00:11:24.084 --> 00:11:25.385
She's the hostess here.

175
00:11:26.887 --> 00:11:29.032
Has anybody left the club since
you made the call to us?

176
00:11:29.056 --> 00:11:32.468
No. No one. We're closed to
other members this evening.

177
00:11:32.492 --> 00:11:34.452
Meaning the killer
could still be in the building.

178
00:11:35.228 --> 00:11:36.797
We need to question
everyone here.

179
00:11:37.798 --> 00:11:39.366
I wanna get out of here.

180
00:11:40.000 --> 00:11:41.778
I have to go.

181
00:11:41.802 --> 00:11:44.113
They're following me.
I can't be here.

182
00:11:44.137 --> 00:11:45.381
It's all right love.

183
00:11:45.405 --> 00:11:48.084
Remember. what the doctor said.

184
00:11:48.108 --> 00:11:50.076
A man's been murdered.

185
00:12:02.989 --> 00:12:06.536
Tilly often sees and hears
things when she's under stress.

186
00:12:06.560 --> 00:12:09.096
The doctor's prescribed pills
for these episodes.

187
00:12:10.464 --> 00:12:12.065
-And you are?
-Clarke Barron.

188
00:12:12.966 --> 00:12:14.000
Her manager.

189
00:12:16.670 --> 00:12:19.215
Is there anyone we can call
for you? Your parents?

190
00:12:19.239 --> 00:12:20.550
No need.

191
00:12:20.574 --> 00:12:22.085
It's a hell of a shock
for a young woman.

192
00:12:22.109 --> 00:12:25.188
Darling. you've known Tilly
all of five minutes.

193
00:12:25.212 --> 00:12:27.457
Tilly will be fine
once she has her rest.

194
00:12:27.481 --> 00:12:29.392
Isn't that right. darling?

195
00:12:29.416 --> 00:12:31.294
Please. Clarkey.
I wanna go home.

196
00:12:31.318 --> 00:12:32.695
Right.

197
00:12:32.719 --> 00:12:35.455
No one leaves until
we've searched the building.

198
00:13:18.165 --> 00:13:19.766
You are not the man.

199
00:13:24.938 --> 00:13:26.039
Alphy?

200
00:13:34.614 --> 00:13:35.558
Gambling?

201
00:13:35.582 --> 00:13:38.761
I am at liberty
to do what I please

202
00:13:38.785 --> 00:13:39.729
outside the church.

203
00:13:39.753 --> 00:13:42.465
Not when it's illegal.
you bloody can't!

204
00:13:42.489 --> 00:13:44.800
And you know it.

205
00:13:44.824 --> 00:13:46.636
Plus. you've managed
to place yourself bang

206
00:13:46.660 --> 00:13:49.138
in the centre
of a murder investigation.

207
00:13:49.162 --> 00:13:50.630
Oh. come on.

208
00:13:51.264 --> 00:13:52.432
I wasn't to know. was I?

209
00:13:54.401 --> 00:13:55.635
Listen...

210
00:13:57.070 --> 00:13:59.215
I'm prepared to turn
a blind eye to the gambling.

211
00:13:59.239 --> 00:14:00.850
Oh. it's big of you. Thanks.

212
00:14:00.874 --> 00:14:02.008
Don't push it.

213
00:14:04.444 --> 00:14:06.856
But I'll need to see you
down the station tomorrow.

214
00:14:06.880 --> 00:14:07.881
What?

215
00:14:12.719 --> 00:14:15.488
You can't seriously be
treating me like a suspect?

216
00:14:17.224 --> 00:14:18.501
Hey. whoever did this
is clearly...

217
00:14:18.525 --> 00:14:19.793
Enough.

218
00:14:23.930 --> 00:14:29.045
Alphy. go home. sober up.
and I'll see you tomorrow

219
00:14:29.069 --> 00:14:30.437
as a witness.

220
00:14:34.307 --> 00:14:36.643
Well. good luck
doing this without me.

221
00:14:38.211 --> 00:14:40.045
I'll give it my best shot.

222
00:14:42.282 --> 00:14:43.726
Right. fellas.

223
00:14:43.750 --> 00:14:46.329
tell me about
the poker game back there.

224
00:14:46.353 --> 00:14:48.231
I should've stayed in the pub.

225
00:14:48.255 --> 00:14:49.723
I should've never
listened to you.

226
00:14:50.523 --> 00:14:51.891
And what about Malcolm?

227
00:14:53.960 --> 00:14:55.271
He was fine when we saw him.

228
00:14:55.295 --> 00:14:57.440
When was that exactly?

229
00:14:57.464 --> 00:15:00.610
This afternoon.
when he took us to the room.

230
00:15:00.634 --> 00:15:03.846
And none of you had any contact
with him again after that?

231
00:15:03.870 --> 00:15:06.315
He didn't come back in the room
to check on the game at all?

232
00:15:06.339 --> 00:15:07.617
Nah.

233
00:15:07.641 --> 00:15:10.443
He knew we wouldn't get rowdy.
so he left us to it.

234
00:15:11.878 --> 00:15:12.946
Malc's an old friend.

235
00:15:14.848 --> 00:15:16.816
He's letting us
use the room to play.

236
00:15:19.286 --> 00:15:20.887
His mother is going
to be devastated.

237
00:15:32.799 --> 00:15:37.337
So. Miss Mayflower.
what brought you here tonight?

238
00:15:38.471 --> 00:15:39.873
Where's Clarke?

239
00:15:41.107 --> 00:15:44.644
Look. I'm interested in hearing
what you have to say. Tilly.

240
00:15:45.211 --> 00:15:46.289
Makes a change.

241
00:15:46.313 --> 00:15:48.457
Mostly. people speak for me.

242
00:15:48.481 --> 00:15:49.949
That must be wearing.

243
00:15:52.552 --> 00:15:55.055
I am a project for him.
all of them.

244
00:15:56.790 --> 00:16:00.403
This business
is full of people trying.

245
00:16:00.427 --> 00:16:04.440
trying to be
someone to... to make it.

246
00:16:04.464 --> 00:16:06.800
To sell something.
sell themselves.

247
00:16:09.669 --> 00:16:11.571
It's all so tiring.

248
00:16:14.641 --> 00:16:16.810
That's why it's nice
to meet that Cathy.

249
00:16:17.610 --> 00:16:19.555
Yeah. she's... she's different.

250
00:16:19.579 --> 00:16:23.059
A real person
who... who thinks for herself.

251
00:16:23.083 --> 00:16:26.052
feels things. and cares.

252
00:16:30.290 --> 00:16:32.325
-Tilly. Can I ask...
-Jean. actually.

253
00:16:32.892 --> 00:16:34.060
Jean Jones.

254
00:16:35.862 --> 00:16:38.064
Tilly Mayflower
isn't my real name.

255
00:16:39.165 --> 00:16:41.644
Even that was chosen for me.

256
00:16:41.668 --> 00:16:44.380
Tell me. had you met Malcolm
before this evening?

257
00:16:44.404 --> 00:16:47.507
-Who?
-The manager of this place.

258
00:16:50.944 --> 00:16:52.479
The man who was found dead?

259
00:16:53.847 --> 00:16:54.848
Oh...

260
00:16:55.382 --> 00:16:56.616
Yeah. of course.

261
00:16:57.083 --> 00:16:58.351
Silly me. erm...

262
00:16:59.352 --> 00:17:01.864
I mean. no. I've never
been here before.

263
00:17:01.888 --> 00:17:05.801
and... I don't really
remember seeing him.

264
00:17:05.825 --> 00:17:09.605
But you did see him because
he closed the club for you.

265
00:17:09.629 --> 00:17:11.564
You thanked him and the hostess.

266
00:17:12.332 --> 00:17:13.566
Did I?

267
00:17:15.335 --> 00:17:18.247
Oh... I can't remember.

268
00:17:18.271 --> 00:17:20.383
You can't remember much.
can you. Tilly?

269
00:17:20.407 --> 00:17:22.342
It's these pills. erm...

270
00:17:24.144 --> 00:17:26.956
There was this lady
looking after us.

271
00:17:26.980 --> 00:17:29.225
but I can't remember her name.

272
00:17:29.249 --> 00:17:30.517
Erm...

273
00:17:32.452 --> 00:17:33.853
Sorry. I...

274
00:17:37.457 --> 00:17:38.968
-Are you all right?
-Yeah...

275
00:17:38.992 --> 00:17:40.959
I just...

276
00:17:42.595 --> 00:17:44.431
feel a little. erm...

277
00:17:46.399 --> 00:17:47.866
Here...

278
00:17:49.569 --> 00:17:52.439
Small sips. big breaths.

279
00:17:57.811 --> 00:17:59.345
Tell me. Tilly.

280
00:18:02.882 --> 00:18:05.752
When was the last time
you had anything to eat. love?

281
00:18:07.720 --> 00:18:08.721
I don't know.

282
00:18:15.161 --> 00:18:16.329
Cheese and pickle?

283
00:18:26.372 --> 00:18:27.540
Mmm.

284
00:18:34.414 --> 00:18:35.582
Mmm...

285
00:18:39.752 --> 00:18:41.855
Can I ask about your episodes?

286
00:18:44.057 --> 00:18:45.935
Do you ever feel out of control?

287
00:18:45.959 --> 00:18:48.661
Do things that perhaps
you don't remember?

288
00:18:49.195 --> 00:18:50.363
Tilly...

289
00:18:52.265 --> 00:18:54.033
Things that are
out of character?

290
00:18:55.635 --> 00:18:58.614
I know what you're suggesting...

291
00:18:58.638 --> 00:19:01.750
But I would never do anything
to intentionally hurt anyone.

292
00:19:01.774 --> 00:19:02.809
I couldn't.

293
00:19:04.511 --> 00:19:05.745
I'm a Buddhist.

294
00:19:11.584 --> 00:19:12.828
I should be with Tilly.

295
00:19:12.852 --> 00:19:14.196
Mmm.

296
00:19:14.220 --> 00:19:15.631
You're not keen on letting her

297
00:19:15.655 --> 00:19:18.100
out of your sight.
are you. Mr Barron. hmm?

298
00:19:18.124 --> 00:19:20.603
What are you so afraid of?

299
00:19:20.627 --> 00:19:23.272
That she'll say something
you're unable to control.

300
00:19:23.296 --> 00:19:24.640
implicate you in some way?

301
00:19:24.664 --> 00:19:27.309
I have absolutely
nothing to hide.

302
00:19:27.333 --> 00:19:30.746
I am a talent manager.
not a serial killer.

303
00:19:30.770 --> 00:19:33.106
The only crimes I deal with
are the ones against fashion.

304
00:19:34.574 --> 00:19:37.544
What does your wife make
of your relationship with Tilly?

305
00:19:41.080 --> 00:19:42.558
A little unethical.
don't you think?

306
00:19:42.582 --> 00:19:44.384
Having an affair with a client.

307
00:19:46.419 --> 00:19:47.863
We can't help who we fall for.

308
00:19:47.887 --> 00:19:51.367
Hmm. See. we found
an envelope full of cash

309
00:19:51.391 --> 00:19:52.735
in Malcolm Riley's pocket.

310
00:19:52.759 --> 00:19:54.303
And we know you asked him
to close the club

311
00:19:54.327 --> 00:19:56.872
for a few hours
to preserve privacy.

312
00:19:56.896 --> 00:20:00.433
Perhaps that was for your
own benefit rather than Tilly's.

313
00:20:01.634 --> 00:20:04.647
Did you pay him
for his discretion?

314
00:20:04.671 --> 00:20:07.607
Did he cotton on to your affair
and ask for more?

315
00:20:09.909 --> 00:20:12.354
Did you lash out.

316
00:20:12.378 --> 00:20:17.383
or did Tilly lash out
and you're covering for her?

317
00:20:19.752 --> 00:20:21.897
Did this affair
cost a man his life?

318
00:20:21.921 --> 00:20:23.866
I fail to see
what our relationship has to do

319
00:20:23.890 --> 00:20:25.401
with any of this nonsense.

320
00:20:25.425 --> 00:20:26.893
-Oh. it's nonsense?
-Yeah.

321
00:20:28.194 --> 00:20:29.338
A man has been murdered.

322
00:20:29.362 --> 00:20:31.574
Not by me.

323
00:20:31.598 --> 00:20:33.208
I've never even met
the man before.

324
00:20:33.232 --> 00:20:36.178
I've barely had
any contact with him.

325
00:20:36.202 --> 00:20:37.646
Look. I hate to speak
ill of the dead.

326
00:20:37.670 --> 00:20:40.849
but he seems rather forgettable.

327
00:20:40.873 --> 00:20:43.752
Perhaps you should
be speaking to that

328
00:20:43.776 --> 00:20:44.954
hostess girl.

329
00:20:44.978 --> 00:20:46.755
And why is that?

330
00:20:46.779 --> 00:20:49.816
I'm an observer
of women's bodies. Detective.

331
00:20:50.383 --> 00:20:51.961
It's my job.

332
00:20:51.985 --> 00:20:55.030
Her body language towards him
was as cold as ice.

333
00:20:55.054 --> 00:20:56.932
Mark my words.

334
00:20:56.956 --> 00:20:58.424
Something happened between them.

335
00:21:02.962 --> 00:21:05.908
Why don't you tell me
about this poker game happening

336
00:21:05.932 --> 00:21:07.066
at the time of the murder?

337
00:21:08.167 --> 00:21:09.469
I didn't know about it.

338
00:21:10.370 --> 00:21:11.714
Well. Surely you had to go
to the kitchen

339
00:21:11.738 --> 00:21:13.983
and the storeroom
to serve your guests.

340
00:21:14.007 --> 00:21:15.007
You didn't hear anything?

341
00:21:16.376 --> 00:21:17.886
Why didn't Malcolm tell you
about the game?

342
00:21:17.910 --> 00:21:21.547
Especially as you were the only
two staff working this evening?

343
00:21:23.249 --> 00:21:24.684
It was illegal. wasn't it?

344
00:21:26.019 --> 00:21:27.920
He probably didn't want
to get in trouble.

345
00:21:29.055 --> 00:21:31.624
Did you and Malcolm
have a trusting relationship?

346
00:21:33.926 --> 00:21:35.270
I suppose.

347
00:21:35.294 --> 00:21:38.564
We have a witness who says
you were being frosty with him.

348
00:21:39.298 --> 00:21:40.600
Why was that?

349
00:21:42.669 --> 00:21:45.347
Did you. in fact
find out about the game?

350
00:21:45.371 --> 00:21:47.750
Did you fall out about it?

351
00:21:47.774 --> 00:21:49.776
-Is that why you attacked him?
-I didn't.

352
00:21:55.915 --> 00:21:57.016
Tell me...

353
00:21:57.583 --> 00:21:59.361
are you Kara with a K?

354
00:21:59.385 --> 00:22:00.987
Yeah. Why?

355
00:22:07.560 --> 00:22:09.362
We found this
in Malcolm's pocket.

356
00:22:16.869 --> 00:22:18.871
Does this money
belong to you. Kara?

357
00:22:19.706 --> 00:22:22.217
-Yeah.
-Why did he have it?

358
00:22:22.241 --> 00:22:23.676
It's my wages.

359
00:22:26.012 --> 00:22:27.313
Are you sure about that?

360
00:22:27.947 --> 00:22:29.391
What did you do to Malcolm?

361
00:22:29.415 --> 00:22:32.051
I didn't do anything to Malcolm.

362
00:22:33.453 --> 00:22:34.630
I don't know what he was up to.

363
00:22:34.654 --> 00:22:36.456
But it had nothing
to do with me.

364
00:22:37.457 --> 00:22:38.991
So he was up to something.

365
00:22:46.566 --> 00:22:48.468
Marcus is usually up by now.

366
00:22:50.603 --> 00:22:53.348
Do you not think
we should leave them alone?

367
00:22:53.372 --> 00:22:55.908
We don't want to intrude
on their time together.

368
00:22:56.709 --> 00:22:57.886
especially as we don't know...

369
00:22:57.910 --> 00:23:00.189
I'm simply going to check
if they need anything.

370
00:23:00.213 --> 00:23:01.423
That's all.

371
00:23:01.447 --> 00:23:02.825
Then we'll go.

372
00:23:02.849 --> 00:23:03.916
Promise.

373
00:23:14.660 --> 00:23:16.696
Raymond. it's Leonard.

374
00:23:18.564 --> 00:23:20.542
-How's your father?
-Shh... he's sleeping.

375
00:23:20.566 --> 00:23:22.044
He had a bad night.

376
00:23:22.068 --> 00:23:23.445
Oh.

377
00:23:23.469 --> 00:23:24.847
I'm sorry to hear that.

378
00:23:24.871 --> 00:23:27.516
It's okay. I'm just trying
to be quiet now so he can rest.

379
00:23:27.540 --> 00:23:29.818
I'm really hungry...

380
00:23:29.842 --> 00:23:33.045
Daniel and I
are on our way to breakfast.

381
00:23:33.913 --> 00:23:35.081
Oh yes.

382
00:23:35.848 --> 00:23:37.326
Yes. we are indeed.

383
00:23:37.350 --> 00:23:39.962
Why don't I write your father
a note to explain

384
00:23:39.986 --> 00:23:42.865
that you've come with us
and you'll be back soon.

385
00:23:42.889 --> 00:23:45.300
How does sausage. egg
chips and beans sound?

386
00:23:45.324 --> 00:23:47.527
Chips? For breakfast?

387
00:23:48.561 --> 00:23:50.239
Come on. Get a scrap of paper

388
00:23:50.263 --> 00:23:51.764
and let's leave
your father in peace.

389
00:23:56.669 --> 00:23:59.448
I know what you're going to say.

390
00:23:59.472 --> 00:24:01.607
That we should get some
fried bread on the side.

391
00:24:11.617 --> 00:24:12.752
Remind me.

392
00:24:13.386 --> 00:24:14.921
why were you at Sady's?

393
00:24:15.755 --> 00:24:16.765
I told you.

394
00:24:16.789 --> 00:24:19.392
Tilly Mayflower would be wearing
a CeCe's dress.

395
00:24:21.127 --> 00:24:22.128
Jam or marmalade?

396
00:24:22.929 --> 00:24:24.030
Half and half. please.

397
00:24:27.233 --> 00:24:29.278
Well. how come Mrs C
wasn't with you?

398
00:24:29.302 --> 00:24:31.246
Why are you asking me
about this?

399
00:24:31.270 --> 00:24:32.915
Shouldn't you be focusing
on finding out

400
00:24:32.939 --> 00:24:34.373
who strangled that poor man?

401
00:24:40.947 --> 00:24:42.014
Why was he there?

402
00:24:43.115 --> 00:24:44.193
Mr Switch?

403
00:24:44.217 --> 00:24:46.652
We're trying to make
CeCe's a success.

404
00:24:48.821 --> 00:24:49.889
Of course.

405
00:24:50.990 --> 00:24:52.801
-Sugar?
-Two please.

406
00:24:52.825 --> 00:24:54.360
Two?

407
00:24:55.127 --> 00:24:56.538
What?

408
00:24:56.562 --> 00:24:58.497
Well. you've only
ever wanted one.

409
00:25:22.788 --> 00:25:25.057
How was Tilly
when you spoke to her?

410
00:25:26.792 --> 00:25:29.438
I'm not sure whether her
erratic behaviour is an act.

411
00:25:29.462 --> 00:25:30.973
No. I don't think so.

412
00:25:30.997 --> 00:25:34.333
The way she clung to me
felt like she needed comfort.

413
00:25:35.568 --> 00:25:38.747
Must be so hard for a young
woman in a world like that.

414
00:25:38.771 --> 00:25:40.706
Constantly under the spotlight.

415
00:25:42.942 --> 00:25:44.043
She's so young. Geordie.

416
00:25:45.478 --> 00:25:47.480
She reminded me of Esme.

417
00:25:48.581 --> 00:25:50.392
What did you make
of her manager?

418
00:25:50.416 --> 00:25:53.419
Very protective. wouldn't
let her out of his sight.

419
00:25:55.254 --> 00:25:56.632
So he was there
the whole evening?

420
00:25:56.656 --> 00:25:57.657
Mmm...

421
00:25:58.124 --> 00:25:59.534
And the hostess.

422
00:25:59.558 --> 00:26:01.226
Oh. she was in and out
with the drinks.

423
00:26:04.196 --> 00:26:05.307
I thought expensive champagne

424
00:26:05.331 --> 00:26:06.942
wasn't supposed
to give you a sore head.

425
00:26:06.966 --> 00:26:09.368
I think it's the volume
that makes the difference.

426
00:26:17.977 --> 00:26:21.623
I found a newspaper report
claiming Tilly Mayflower

427
00:26:21.647 --> 00:26:24.559
got in a rage
and pushed a photographer.

428
00:26:24.583 --> 00:26:26.752
Tilly does seem to be
a bit of a live wire.

429
00:26:27.954 --> 00:26:29.555
But she also has several alibis.

430
00:26:31.390 --> 00:26:33.902
Plus. I mean.
she's 90 pounds soaking wet.

431
00:26:33.926 --> 00:26:37.139
so unlikely to have
overpowered Malcolm Riley.

432
00:26:37.163 --> 00:26:38.840
Anything on Clarke Barron?

433
00:26:38.864 --> 00:26:40.066
Investigated for fraud.

434
00:26:41.867 --> 00:26:43.712
-Oh. yeah.
-Found to be innocent.

435
00:26:43.736 --> 00:26:44.737
Oh.

436
00:26:45.571 --> 00:26:47.049
Kara. The hostess.

437
00:26:47.073 --> 00:26:49.818
She claims not to have known
the poker game was happening.

438
00:26:49.842 --> 00:26:50.943
But I'm not so sure.

439
00:26:55.681 --> 00:26:57.683
-You all right?
-No.

440
00:26:58.184 --> 00:26:59.528
I can't sit.

441
00:26:59.552 --> 00:27:02.521
I can't stand and don't even
get me started on sleeping.

442
00:27:04.357 --> 00:27:05.825
Larry. Hmm.

443
00:27:09.662 --> 00:27:13.942
Honestly. I'm not sure how much
longer we can keep this up.

444
00:27:13.966 --> 00:27:16.802
At some point. we're gonna
have to make a decision.

445
00:27:17.970 --> 00:27:19.305
I have to go to the bathroom.

446
00:27:22.041 --> 00:27:23.151
She's been crying a lot.

447
00:27:23.175 --> 00:27:26.412
That happens. I don't think
it's just the pregnancy

448
00:27:27.246 --> 00:27:28.924
I'll talk to her.

449
00:27:28.948 --> 00:27:32.627
In the meantime. can you speak
to Malcolm Riley's mother?

450
00:27:32.651 --> 00:27:34.763
Find out anything you can
about his work life

451
00:27:34.787 --> 00:27:37.199
and his relationship with Kara.

452
00:27:37.223 --> 00:27:39.058
I need to make some phone calls.

453
00:27:40.793 --> 00:27:42.504
Where's all this
money coming from?

454
00:27:42.528 --> 00:27:45.374
We haven't sold that much stock.

455
00:27:45.398 --> 00:27:48.210
-It doesn't add up.
-Oh...

456
00:27:48.234 --> 00:27:50.703
That is quite an imbalance.

457
00:27:51.370 --> 00:27:52.738
It's that Mr Switch.

458
00:27:53.506 --> 00:27:55.617
He's up to something.

459
00:27:55.641 --> 00:27:57.152
He's got Cathy
in the palm of his hand.

460
00:27:57.176 --> 00:27:58.587
she won't hear
a word against him.

461
00:27:58.611 --> 00:28:02.748
But these figures prove there is
something very definitely amiss.

462
00:28:04.950 --> 00:28:06.528
Time for drastic measures.

463
00:28:06.552 --> 00:28:08.730
Oh. no. no. No. Sylvia.

464
00:28:08.754 --> 00:28:11.366
Let's start by going through
all his personal papers

465
00:28:11.390 --> 00:28:14.102
see if we can find
anything incriminating.

466
00:28:14.126 --> 00:28:17.906
And we'll have to track
his movements. work out where

467
00:28:17.930 --> 00:28:19.374
this money is coming from.

468
00:28:19.398 --> 00:28:21.734
-We?
-No secret agent works alone.

469
00:28:55.835 --> 00:28:57.002
Well. this is different.

470
00:29:00.439 --> 00:29:01.807
Thanks for coming in.

471
00:29:03.609 --> 00:29:05.044
Not like I had a choice.

472
00:29:07.713 --> 00:29:09.324
So...

473
00:29:09.348 --> 00:29:11.359
you don't want me
on the other side anymore. then?

474
00:29:11.383 --> 00:29:13.528
You can't come along
and investigate crimes

475
00:29:13.552 --> 00:29:15.588
if you're
a bloody criminal. Alphy.

476
00:29:16.622 --> 00:29:18.891
I'm here as a witness. Geordie.

477
00:29:21.060 --> 00:29:22.828
What's going on with you?

478
00:29:30.302 --> 00:29:34.673
Right. can you tell me what you
remember about the poker game?

479
00:29:35.774 --> 00:29:37.352
Hmm.

480
00:29:37.376 --> 00:29:38.611
Er...

481
00:29:39.578 --> 00:29:42.257
I met Leighton at the pub.
we got chatting.

482
00:29:42.281 --> 00:29:43.892
he mentioned a game.
I thought. why not.

483
00:29:43.916 --> 00:29:45.594
Malcolm Riley
showed us to the room.

484
00:29:45.618 --> 00:29:47.129
handed over a bottle of scotch

485
00:29:47.153 --> 00:29:49.555
and some glasses.
we started playing.

486
00:29:50.856 --> 00:29:52.300
I didn't see him again
after that.

487
00:29:52.324 --> 00:29:53.568
So you four

488
00:29:53.592 --> 00:29:55.470
-were the only ones in the room.
-Mmm.

489
00:29:55.494 --> 00:29:57.630
Uh... Well.
apart from the hostess.

490
00:30:00.065 --> 00:30:01.133
-The hostess?
-Mmm.

491
00:30:02.801 --> 00:30:03.845
Are you sure?

492
00:30:03.869 --> 00:30:05.804
I wasn't that drunk. Geordie.

493
00:30:06.505 --> 00:30:07.907
How drunk were you?

494
00:30:09.775 --> 00:30:10.876
Is that relevant?

495
00:30:12.344 --> 00:30:14.456
Well. you've always known
when to stop.

496
00:30:14.480 --> 00:30:17.726
So I can't have a few drinks
without being judged.

497
00:30:17.750 --> 00:30:21.129
I'm just trying to work out what
happened to the Alphy I know.

498
00:30:21.153 --> 00:30:24.456
-And why do you care?
-Because I'm your mate?

499
00:30:25.658 --> 00:30:27.626
I don't understand
where this is coming from.

500
00:30:35.868 --> 00:30:37.770
You were asking
about the hostess?

501
00:30:39.338 --> 00:30:42.184
-Yes.
-Yeah. she was there

502
00:30:42.208 --> 00:30:43.818
and pretty incompetent with it.

503
00:30:43.842 --> 00:30:47.556
She... she spilled a drink
all over me.

504
00:30:47.580 --> 00:30:48.757
Insisted on cleaning it up.

505
00:30:48.781 --> 00:30:50.883
I just wanted
to get on with the game.

506
00:30:53.552 --> 00:30:54.930
Could that
have been a distraction

507
00:30:54.954 --> 00:30:56.355
to get a look at your cards?

508
00:30:58.824 --> 00:31:00.392
Well. she was odd.

509
00:31:02.828 --> 00:31:05.698
She came in and plunked ice
and lemon in our glasses.

510
00:31:06.765 --> 00:31:07.976
Now. we were all drinking neat

511
00:31:08.000 --> 00:31:10.312
and since when do you
put lemon in neat whiskey?

512
00:31:10.336 --> 00:31:12.805
And was it the same amount
of ice in each glass?

513
00:31:14.139 --> 00:31:15.917
No.

514
00:31:15.941 --> 00:31:19.854
No. now I think about it.
It was... very random.

515
00:31:19.878 --> 00:31:21.046
And the lemon.

516
00:31:21.847 --> 00:31:23.015
Or deliberate?

517
00:31:24.250 --> 00:31:25.751
-To give signals to...
-Leighton.

518
00:31:28.087 --> 00:31:30.298
Yeah. I would've beaten him.

519
00:31:30.322 --> 00:31:33.301
I mean. I had a weak hand.
but he had nothing.

520
00:31:33.325 --> 00:31:34.536
He could only have been
that confident.

521
00:31:34.560 --> 00:31:36.095
bluffing if he knew my hand.

522
00:31:39.898 --> 00:31:42.334
It sounds like
the whole thing was a sting.

523
00:31:45.337 --> 00:31:46.505
Ah...

524
00:31:47.172 --> 00:31:48.350
Oh. my word.

525
00:31:48.374 --> 00:31:49.941
I shouldn't have had
that third sausage.

526
00:31:50.876 --> 00:31:52.721
But I'm so full
you and Leonard are gonna

527
00:31:52.745 --> 00:31:54.445
have to roll me down the street.

528
00:31:59.151 --> 00:32:00.428
What cake is that?

529
00:32:00.452 --> 00:32:02.197
Looks like black forest gateau.

530
00:32:02.221 --> 00:32:04.165
You can't still be hungry.

531
00:32:04.189 --> 00:32:05.491
It's my dad's favourite.

532
00:32:07.860 --> 00:32:09.337
I forgot to get bread.

533
00:32:09.361 --> 00:32:10.763
Won't be a tick.

534
00:32:13.832 --> 00:32:14.967
It'll be all right.

535
00:32:15.701 --> 00:32:17.078
I promise.

536
00:32:17.102 --> 00:32:18.337
You won't be alone.

537
00:32:22.908 --> 00:32:23.909
Oh. my word.

538
00:32:25.844 --> 00:32:27.046
{\an8}Black Forest Gateau.

539
00:32:30.349 --> 00:32:31.917
You're such a good lad.

540
00:32:36.021 --> 00:32:37.389
If only I could be there.

541
00:32:46.765 --> 00:32:48.633
This looks too delicious
for words.

542
00:34:03.208 --> 00:34:04.843
Lovely hat. Mrs C.

543
00:34:13.752 --> 00:34:15.864
Alphy says they only
saw Malcolm Riley

544
00:34:15.888 --> 00:34:18.757
once that evening
when he showed them in here.

545
00:34:21.527 --> 00:34:23.595
But the whole game
feels like a setup.

546
00:34:29.701 --> 00:34:30.945
What time do you make it?

547
00:34:30.969 --> 00:34:32.504
Quarter past two.

548
00:34:33.872 --> 00:34:35.574
That's a half hour slow.

549
00:34:37.609 --> 00:34:40.345
Well. either it's not been
wound up properly.

550
00:34:41.213 --> 00:34:42.815
or it's been deliberately
tampered with.

551
00:34:48.687 --> 00:34:50.965
You've been lying
to us all along.

552
00:34:50.989 --> 00:34:53.168
You were part of this thing.
weren't you. Kara?

553
00:34:53.192 --> 00:34:54.369
No idea
what you're talking about.

554
00:34:54.393 --> 00:34:56.171
You were using
ice cubes in their drinks

555
00:34:56.195 --> 00:34:58.630
to signal to Leighton. Hmm?

556
00:35:00.499 --> 00:35:02.777
And what was Malcolm's
involvement in all of this?

557
00:35:02.801 --> 00:35:05.046
Did you and Leighton
decide to cut him out?

558
00:35:05.070 --> 00:35:06.181
-Is that why you murdered him?
-No.

559
00:35:06.205 --> 00:35:07.949
I don't know what happened!

560
00:35:07.973 --> 00:35:10.042
But we've got
a pretty good idea. Kara.

561
00:35:11.543 --> 00:35:13.812
It'll be a lot worse for you
if you don't tell us.

562
00:35:18.350 --> 00:35:20.228
Me. Malcolm and Leighton.

563
00:35:20.252 --> 00:35:22.020
we fixed the game
for Leighton to win.

564
00:35:23.589 --> 00:35:25.500
Malcolm was nervous.
but Leighton convinced him

565
00:35:25.524 --> 00:35:27.502
he could make us all money.

566
00:35:27.526 --> 00:35:30.171
Do you think it's possible
that Malcolm changed his mind?

567
00:35:30.195 --> 00:35:32.240
Got cold feet?

568
00:35:32.264 --> 00:35:35.501
He wanted the money to put
towards a house for his mother.

569
00:35:37.002 --> 00:35:39.481
But he was worried
he was going to lose his job.

570
00:35:39.505 --> 00:35:40.906
Malcolm was weak.

571
00:35:42.908 --> 00:35:45.520
I hadn't met Leighton before.
but I've got the feeling he was

572
00:35:45.544 --> 00:35:47.613
a difficult person to say no to.

573
00:35:49.248 --> 00:35:51.559
How well did you know Leighton?

574
00:35:51.583 --> 00:35:53.795
Myself and Drew are old friends.

575
00:35:53.819 --> 00:35:55.430
We met Leighton at our local
a couple of times.

576
00:35:55.454 --> 00:35:57.532
and he invited us
for a game of poker.

577
00:35:57.556 --> 00:35:59.567
And you'd never
met Malcolm before?

578
00:35:59.591 --> 00:36:01.069
No.

579
00:36:01.093 --> 00:36:03.238
But Leighton said
Malcolm was a mate

580
00:36:03.262 --> 00:36:05.473
and he'd let us play
at the club undisturbed.

581
00:36:05.497 --> 00:36:06.941
He was pretty keen
on having the game.

582
00:36:06.965 --> 00:36:09.010
He said it'd be free booze
and winner takes all.

583
00:36:09.034 --> 00:36:10.102
We thought. "Why not?"

584
00:36:10.969 --> 00:36:12.180
Makes a change from a few pints

585
00:36:12.204 --> 00:36:15.116
and a game of darts
in our local.

586
00:36:15.140 --> 00:36:18.119
At what point did you discover
the game was fixed?

587
00:36:18.143 --> 00:36:20.388
-What?
-I'm afraid so.

588
00:36:20.412 --> 00:36:24.826
You. Kevin and Alphy.
you were all set up.

589
00:36:24.850 --> 00:36:28.696
No wonder he was so pushy
about the game.

590
00:36:28.720 --> 00:36:30.865
And getting
that vicar involved too.

591
00:36:30.889 --> 00:36:31.924
He lost the most.

592
00:36:33.225 --> 00:36:34.993
How did Leighton behave
during the game?

593
00:36:37.129 --> 00:36:40.608
He was confident. Mmm.

594
00:36:40.632 --> 00:36:44.445
Cocky. even. Kev felt bad
for the vicar bloke.

595
00:36:44.469 --> 00:36:46.114
Tried to warn him.
if he didn't have

596
00:36:46.138 --> 00:36:47.549
a strong hand he should fold.

597
00:36:47.573 --> 00:36:49.083
How did Leighton react

598
00:36:49.107 --> 00:36:51.152
when Kevin
tried to help the vicar?

599
00:36:51.176 --> 00:36:52.687
Oh. he wasn't there.

600
00:36:52.711 --> 00:36:54.255
Where was he?

601
00:36:54.279 --> 00:36:55.747
In the gents.

602
00:36:56.248 --> 00:36:57.592
What time was this?

603
00:36:57.616 --> 00:37:00.562
About 8:15. I was half cut.

604
00:37:00.586 --> 00:37:02.463
but I do remember
looking at the clock

605
00:37:02.487 --> 00:37:04.599
because I was a bit worried
about the missus going off

606
00:37:04.623 --> 00:37:06.391
at me for getting in late.

607
00:37:06.925 --> 00:37:08.126
The clock on the wall?

608
00:37:09.261 --> 00:37:10.429
Yeah.

609
00:37:13.665 --> 00:37:16.311
That poker game
was very important to you.

610
00:37:16.335 --> 00:37:18.112
wasn't it. Leighton?

611
00:37:18.136 --> 00:37:22.407
Important enough that you would
alter a clock to slow down time

612
00:37:23.675 --> 00:37:25.386
making your opponents
think they hadn't been

613
00:37:25.410 --> 00:37:27.478
playing for as long as they had.

614
00:37:30.449 --> 00:37:31.793
<i>And by changing the clock.</i>

615
00:37:31.817 --> 00:37:33.928
<i>you also allowed yourself
to have an alibi</i>

616
00:37:33.952 --> 00:37:35.320
<i>for the time of the murder.</i>

617
00:37:36.154 --> 00:37:37.632
<i>As the others believed it to be</i>

618
00:37:37.656 --> 00:37:40.625
<i>half an hour earlier
than it actually was.</i>

619
00:37:44.396 --> 00:37:48.000
You're the only person who left
the room during the poker game.

620
00:37:49.301 --> 00:37:50.979
I've done the walk
from the cloakroom

621
00:37:51.003 --> 00:37:53.081
down to the poker room and back.

622
00:37:53.105 --> 00:37:55.316
Plenty of time to strangle a man

623
00:37:55.340 --> 00:37:58.252
and be back in your seat
cards in hand.

624
00:37:58.276 --> 00:38:00.488
without your
inebriated fellow players

625
00:38:00.512 --> 00:38:02.314
noticing a hair out of place.

626
00:38:04.082 --> 00:38:05.460
You were also helped by the fact

627
00:38:05.484 --> 00:38:07.428
that the club
was closed to anyone else.

628
00:38:07.452 --> 00:38:09.530
-Cheers!
-You sound lovely.

629
00:38:09.554 --> 00:38:13.334
<i>Apart from Tilly Mayflower
and her guests. all distracted</i>

630
00:38:13.358 --> 00:38:16.938
<i>by vast quantities
of expensive champagne.</i>

631
00:38:16.962 --> 00:38:20.008
When I spoke to you
shortly after we found his body.

632
00:38:20.032 --> 00:38:21.633
you seemed upset

633
00:38:22.501 --> 00:38:24.836
but not shocked about Malcolm.

634
00:38:25.404 --> 00:38:26.638
Was that remorse?

635
00:38:31.076 --> 00:38:34.122
You. Kara and Malcolm
were in on it together.

636
00:38:34.146 --> 00:38:36.815
Only Malcolm was the weak link.

637
00:38:37.983 --> 00:38:39.794
Is it possible he wanted out?

638
00:38:39.818 --> 00:38:41.262
Because that's what
you were arguing about

639
00:38:41.286 --> 00:38:42.754
in the cloakroom. weren't you?

640
00:38:44.456 --> 00:38:46.792
You weren't gonna
let him ruin it for you.

641
00:39:00.872 --> 00:39:01.940
Take your time.

642
00:39:03.942 --> 00:39:05.677
It's been tough recently.

643
00:39:09.047 --> 00:39:11.392
My boss threatened to fire me.

644
00:39:11.416 --> 00:39:14.429
and I got a ton of bills
overdue. it just got...

645
00:39:14.453 --> 00:39:15.954
It all just got too much.

646
00:39:17.556 --> 00:39:20.301
I really needed that cash.

647
00:39:20.325 --> 00:39:22.461
Tell us
what happened with Malcolm.

648
00:39:25.230 --> 00:39:26.798
He said we should end the game

649
00:39:27.799 --> 00:39:29.444
and give everyone
their money back.

650
00:39:29.468 --> 00:39:31.212
I've been angry before. but...

651
00:39:31.236 --> 00:39:33.304
<i>This time I couldn't stop.</i>

652
00:39:34.706 --> 00:39:38.453
I knew when I had my hands
around his neck. I should stop.

653
00:39:38.477 --> 00:39:40.144
<i>But I just couldn't.</i>

654
00:39:53.925 --> 00:39:55.026
I was desperate.

655
00:40:02.033 --> 00:40:04.069
If only you could turn
the clock back now. eh?

656
00:40:40.839 --> 00:40:42.474
Why are you locking up?

657
00:40:43.208 --> 00:40:44.585
I'm not opening this afternoon.

658
00:40:44.609 --> 00:40:47.789
I beg your pardon.
It's a church. not a grocer's.

659
00:40:47.813 --> 00:40:50.825
Yeah. well. I doubt
I'd be of much use to anyone.

660
00:40:50.849 --> 00:40:52.994
Look. Alphy.
we need to make a plan

661
00:40:53.018 --> 00:40:56.631
for what's going to happen
to Raymond after Marcus dies.

662
00:40:56.655 --> 00:40:59.700
We're all rallying around
right now and everyone's doing

663
00:40:59.724 --> 00:41:01.803
an admirable job
of chipping in to help.

664
00:41:01.827 --> 00:41:04.472
But Raymond's going
to need full-time care

665
00:41:04.496 --> 00:41:06.908
and very possibly
sooner than we think.

666
00:41:06.932 --> 00:41:09.334
We need to know
where he's going to end up.

667
00:41:10.302 --> 00:41:12.404
Have you informed
Children's Services?

668
00:41:14.840 --> 00:41:16.818
He might need to be
in the care of a boy's home.

669
00:41:16.842 --> 00:41:18.386
Those places are awful.

670
00:41:18.410 --> 00:41:19.821
Well. they were
good enough for me.

671
00:41:19.845 --> 00:41:21.889
The Church
should be helping him.

672
00:41:21.913 --> 00:41:25.226
Leonard. I'm a vicar.
not a social worker.

673
00:41:25.250 --> 00:41:26.294
By all means. make him yours.

674
00:41:26.318 --> 00:41:27.986
But that child
is not my problem.

675
00:42:08.360 --> 00:42:09.403
Cathy.

676
00:42:09.427 --> 00:42:11.439
I am busy. Sylvia.

677
00:42:11.463 --> 00:42:12.797
This can't wait.

678
00:42:13.965 --> 00:42:15.367
It's Mr Switch.

679
00:42:16.501 --> 00:42:19.547
He's a confidence trickster...
a swindler.

680
00:42:19.571 --> 00:42:20.948
What are you talking about?

681
00:42:20.972 --> 00:42:22.183
We observed him.

682
00:42:22.207 --> 00:42:24.852
He met a lady friend.
gave her flowers

683
00:42:24.876 --> 00:42:26.621
and then took
papers of hers to the bank

684
00:42:26.645 --> 00:42:29.347
to steal her money no doubt.

685
00:42:30.415 --> 00:42:31.650
You mean his sister.

686
00:42:33.385 --> 00:42:34.462
Beg pardon?

687
00:42:34.486 --> 00:42:35.563
He's signing the papers

688
00:42:35.587 --> 00:42:37.298
for his sister
to get a bank loan.

689
00:42:37.322 --> 00:42:39.457
You know. like Jack did
for us to get this place.

690
00:42:41.059 --> 00:42:42.427
Oh. my word.

691
00:42:43.428 --> 00:42:44.538
did you and Jack follow him?

692
00:42:44.562 --> 00:42:46.173
There is something amiss.

693
00:42:46.197 --> 00:42:47.441
I can't believe this.

694
00:42:47.465 --> 00:42:49.010
I saw this with my own eyes.

695
00:42:49.034 --> 00:42:50.100
Sylvia...

696
00:42:51.503 --> 00:42:54.081
Sorry to interrupt...

697
00:42:54.105 --> 00:42:55.516
I know I don't have
an appointment.

698
00:42:55.540 --> 00:42:57.575
but I could really do
with your help.

699
00:43:08.687 --> 00:43:10.121
Is this what I think it is?

700
00:43:16.594 --> 00:43:19.331
I wish I didn't have to lose
my best member of staff.

701
00:43:20.432 --> 00:43:21.866
No offence to your old man.

702
00:43:26.905 --> 00:43:29.107
And I wish you were
Chief Inspector now.

703
00:43:31.042 --> 00:43:33.821
Even then. I wouldn't be able
to change the policy.

704
00:43:33.845 --> 00:43:36.257
A married woman
cannot work in the force.

705
00:43:36.281 --> 00:43:37.482
You knew that.

706
00:43:38.416 --> 00:43:40.118
Hey. it'll be all right.

707
00:43:42.754 --> 00:43:43.822
Just...

708
00:43:45.824 --> 00:43:48.436
You know. parenting
is the best job in the world.

709
00:43:48.460 --> 00:43:50.095
So you should grab it...

710
00:43:51.029 --> 00:43:52.130
just drink it in.

711
00:43:53.098 --> 00:43:55.300
Because as quick
as a flash. it's over.

712
00:43:56.668 --> 00:43:58.503
And they don't need you anymore.

713
00:44:00.472 --> 00:44:02.950
I have missed so many
precious moments.

714
00:44:02.974 --> 00:44:04.352
and I'll never get them back.

715
00:44:04.376 --> 00:44:06.077
Because I put work first.

716
00:44:24.095 --> 00:44:25.497
The difference is. Geordie.

717
00:44:26.331 --> 00:44:27.699
you had a choice.

718
00:44:33.171 --> 00:44:34.472
Everything okay?

719
00:44:36.341 --> 00:44:38.442
Woah...

720
00:44:39.978 --> 00:44:41.055
How do you feel?

721
00:44:41.079 --> 00:44:43.391
Like Jean Jones.

722
00:44:43.415 --> 00:44:44.892
Well. you look like her as well.

723
00:44:44.916 --> 00:44:47.928
For the first time in my life.
I feel like I'm being true

724
00:44:47.952 --> 00:44:49.854
to who I am. who I really am.

725
00:44:50.588 --> 00:44:51.532
To Jean!

726
00:44:51.556 --> 00:44:54.568
That is the most
important thing. my darling.

727
00:44:54.592 --> 00:44:57.661
Thank you. so. so much.

728
00:44:59.230 --> 00:45:00.608
What the hell
are you playing at?

729
00:45:00.632 --> 00:45:02.067
You can't just wander off.

730
00:45:02.834 --> 00:45:03.978
Come on.

731
00:45:04.002 --> 00:45:05.312
I don't think so.

732
00:45:05.336 --> 00:45:07.615
We happen to be
in the middle of a fitting.

733
00:45:07.639 --> 00:45:10.117
So. I'm going to ask you
to leave our premises

734
00:45:10.141 --> 00:45:12.186
and give the lady some privacy.

735
00:45:12.210 --> 00:45:15.013
I'm going nowhere without Tilly.

736
00:45:16.581 --> 00:45:18.926
You best go find her. then.

737
00:45:18.950 --> 00:45:21.386
Jean has more clothes to try on.

738
00:45:22.320 --> 00:45:24.432
What are you talking about?

739
00:45:24.456 --> 00:45:27.559
Don't be so ridiculous.
you stupid girl.

740
00:45:28.893 --> 00:45:29.894
You're fired.

741
00:45:30.628 --> 00:45:31.663
What?

742
00:45:33.164 --> 00:45:34.332
You heard her.

743
00:45:35.033 --> 00:45:36.410
You're fired.

744
00:45:36.434 --> 00:45:37.769
Now sling your hook.

745
00:45:39.771 --> 00:45:40.772
You need to leave.

746
00:45:43.441 --> 00:45:45.920
You are done.

747
00:45:45.944 --> 00:45:47.621
On the contrary.

748
00:45:47.645 --> 00:45:49.514
She's just getting started.

749
00:45:55.854 --> 00:45:56.987
Oh...

750
00:46:06.798 --> 00:46:08.533
Not a good time.

751
00:46:09.434 --> 00:46:10.802
Open the door. Alphy.

752
00:46:30.588 --> 00:46:32.433
Well. come in. why don't you?

753
00:46:32.457 --> 00:46:33.868
I thought you should know
Leighton confessed

754
00:46:33.892 --> 00:46:35.059
to killing Malcolm Riley.

755
00:46:36.561 --> 00:46:38.038
Well. I can't believe
I didn't see it.

756
00:46:38.062 --> 00:46:40.098
Hmm... Well. you were pie-eyed.

757
00:46:42.800 --> 00:46:45.446
Yeah. Okay. I should have
suspected something.

758
00:46:45.470 --> 00:46:47.105
Don't make this
about you. Alphy.

759
00:46:48.439 --> 00:46:50.375
Well. is he
your new sidekick. is he?

760
00:46:57.081 --> 00:46:58.459
Actually. Leonard came to see me

761
00:46:58.483 --> 00:47:00.385
because he was
worried about you.

762
00:47:01.452 --> 00:47:03.164
And he's not the only one.

763
00:47:03.188 --> 00:47:04.732
You've been
neglecting your duties.

764
00:47:04.756 --> 00:47:07.701
Oh. for goodness' sake. Leonard.
is this about the kid again?

765
00:47:07.725 --> 00:47:09.837
You aren't prepared
to help look after a child

766
00:47:09.861 --> 00:47:12.806
who is about to be orphaned
but you can quite happily

767
00:47:12.830 --> 00:47:16.677
hole up in some seedy club
and gamble with a murderer.

768
00:47:16.701 --> 00:47:18.541
And they'd better not
have been vicarage funds.

769
00:47:21.406 --> 00:47:22.983
Of course not.

770
00:47:23.007 --> 00:47:24.652
Why should I believe you?

771
00:47:24.676 --> 00:47:26.787
You're not behaving
in a very Christian manner

772
00:47:26.811 --> 00:47:28.989
and you are certainly
not behaving

773
00:47:29.013 --> 00:47:30.624
as a man of the cloth should.

774
00:47:30.648 --> 00:47:32.059
You mean how you would.

775
00:47:32.083 --> 00:47:35.729
You don't know how privileged
you are to hold such a position.

776
00:47:35.753 --> 00:47:37.965
-Privilege?
-Everything I went through.

777
00:47:37.989 --> 00:47:39.934
I never lost faith. not once.

778
00:47:39.958 --> 00:47:42.169
Even when it felt as if
everything was against me.

779
00:47:42.193 --> 00:47:43.337
I still clung on to...

780
00:47:43.361 --> 00:47:45.472
Oh. give it a rest
will you. Leonard?

781
00:47:45.496 --> 00:47:48.566
Look. I'm sorry the bishop
rejected you. really I am.

782
00:47:49.934 --> 00:47:51.812
But look at what you have got.

783
00:47:51.836 --> 00:47:53.614
You do God's work running
the halfway house.

784
00:47:53.638 --> 00:47:54.782
you get to live
with your partner

785
00:47:54.806 --> 00:47:57.051
and yet. here you are.
Still clinging on

786
00:47:57.075 --> 00:47:58.710
to the past for dear life.

787
00:47:59.611 --> 00:48:01.222
Hang on.

788
00:48:01.246 --> 00:48:02.423
That's a bit rich. isn't it?

789
00:48:02.447 --> 00:48:04.525
-What?
-Your mother.

790
00:48:04.549 --> 00:48:06.660
-What about her?
-The way she treated you?

791
00:48:06.684 --> 00:48:07.962
Is that why you're
behaving like this?

792
00:48:07.986 --> 00:48:10.622
Rejecting everyone around you
who's trying to help!

793
00:48:12.690 --> 00:48:15.336
You would not have a job
if it weren't for me

794
00:48:15.360 --> 00:48:16.837
helping you over the years.

795
00:48:16.861 --> 00:48:18.806
And now what.
you want to chuck it all in.

796
00:48:18.830 --> 00:48:20.474
put yourself
out there to pasture

797
00:48:20.498 --> 00:48:21.742
in some mind-numbing desk job.

798
00:48:21.766 --> 00:48:24.669
And ignore me...
like you do your family.

799
00:48:28.439 --> 00:48:31.042
You are not a copper.

800
00:48:32.110 --> 00:48:33.611
You've only just noticed?

801
00:48:35.346 --> 00:48:38.316
You can't exactly
call yourself a vicar. either.

802
00:48:41.452 --> 00:48:46.333
You know what I'm...
I'm not listening to any more

803
00:48:46.357 --> 00:48:50.028
of this hypocritical.
sanctimonious rubbish.

804
00:48:50.795 --> 00:48:52.330
And I want you to leave.

805
00:48:53.531 --> 00:48:54.532
Now.

806
00:49:00.972 --> 00:49:04.676
I've tried with you.
Alphy. I really have.

807
00:49:05.543 --> 00:49:09.080
I have given you
friendship. support...

808
00:49:10.381 --> 00:49:11.916
love. even.

809
00:49:13.951 --> 00:49:15.963
But I'm tired of it all.

810
00:49:15.987 --> 00:49:17.088
You have your wish.

811
00:49:18.056 --> 00:49:19.857
From now on. you're on your own.
